</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravensonghausakluif>Ravensong Hausakluif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/15/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Report Feedback</span><hr size=1> Just a few comments on the feedback to this report:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;With that said, what happens with the style review will likely have some sort of impact on this.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
We've been promised pie-in-the-sky results from the &quot;styles review&quot; for over a year.  We hear it's going to happen, then we hear it's going to happen, then we hear it's going to happen some more.  Over a year of it (I know this because I stopped playing my skald over a year ago when I first heard we were going to reap the largesse of the mythical Mythic styles review).  Why should we believe that something positive is suddenly going to spring into existence for Skalds that will amazingly balance out all of their problems?  Some may be hanging on Mythic's every word regarding this, but not all of us believe the company is going to/able to make it happen.  After this many months of unfulfilled promise, it's a little hard to believe the tale.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;We can keep an eye on this, but skalds seem to be doing a lot better in RvR then they were before the 1.65 changes.&quot; </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
When I was 6 years old and played football, I was not very good.  When I was 10 years old and played football, I seemed &quot;to be doing a lot better&quot; than I was before I turned 10.  Do you think that means I could compete with high school or college football players?<br>
Skalds' future value in RvR shouldn't be compared solely to their previous value in RvR.  It should be compared to all the other classes.  An improvement from 'poor' to 'ok' shouldn't really be the goal.  In any case, based on responses like this to previous reports it most likely translates to: &quot;We think you're fine despite your protestations--issue closed.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;This is a bug and an annoying one at that. Make sure it's on the bug forum so our QA folks can make sure it's in the bug tracker.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
You've got to be kidding on this one.  The QA folks should have 2 years worth of data collected on this already.  Everyone that's ever played a skald has complained about this.  How many times does this need to be reported on every forum, and for how many years?  I think I've probably seen this mentioned on every board it could be mentioned on--I've even seen it on the IGN server boards.  This sounds a little like stonewalling.  If it can't be fixed, just tell us and we'll drop the subject.  Acting like you've never heard of the problem paints a much less attractive picture of Mythic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot; 6 different resist chants is too many. This is on the list for us to address, perhaps by combining them down to 2 or 3 chants with 3 or 2 resist types.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Skalds asked for this a long time ago.  It was then given to Paladins who <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>didn't</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ask for it at the time.  I remember this vividly. We're still incredulous.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;This is the case for many classes that choose to spend &quot;left over&quot; points in parry. Is this is just another way of talking about skald defense?&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
These 17 points of parry are the only &quot;defense&quot; a skald has, making them (defensively) one of the worst Warrior/Rogue classes in the game.  In high level RvR this can't even be considered a defense.  If that's how Mythic intends the class to be then case-closed.  If not, then somebody needs to look at our defensive abilities.  It does lend itself well to the current &quot;cookie cutter&quot; outlook for Skalds.  That may also be as intended by Mythic.<br>
<br>
*sigh*<br>
Ravensong<br>
Mig/Guin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sligg0rz>Sligg0rz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/16/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Report Feedback</span><hr size=1> For some people the glass is always half empty...<br>
<br>
&quot;We've been promised pie-in-the-sky results from the &quot;styles review&quot; for over a year. We hear it's going to happen, then we hear it's going to happen, then we hear it's going to happen some more. Over a year of it (I know this because I stopped playing my skald over a year ago when I first heard we were going to reap the largesse of the mythical Mythic styles review). Why should we believe that something positive is suddenly going to spring into existence for Skalds that will amazingly balance out all of their problems? Some may be hanging on Mythic's every word regarding this, but not all of us believe the company is going to/able to make it happen. After this many months of unfulfilled promise, it's a little hard to believe the tale.&quot;<br>
<br>
The skald changes in 1.65 put skalds in a much better place than they were before. They are more effective and useful imo than Thanes, Champs and Minstrels (if you remove SoS from the equation, which is a realm issue more than a class issue) . Hanging on their every word? They made some pretty substantial changes for the class. The higher level shouts were a big deal. As a 50 BS skald I do a LOT more damage than I was doing previously. I am not expecting more Skald love because I don't think we need it.<br>
<br>
We aren't going to get better defense. That has been stated explicitly. Live with it. We will never have the weaponskill of a pure melee. Live with it. We are a a melee hybrid. With my shouts included I do a ton more damage than a Warrior. I may not survive as long, but I do a lot of damage.<br>
<br>
&quot;When I was 6 years old and played football, I was not very good. When I was 10 years old and played football, I seemed &quot;to be doing a lot better&quot; than I was before I turned 10. Do you think that means I could compete with high school or college football players?&quot;<br>
<br>
Stop whining. My Skald beats virtually every class in the game 1 vs 1. In group RvR, if I play my role correctly I can turn the tide more than any single tank. Your opinion about Skalds is probably reflective of your skill with one. You are trying to find a reason for why you suck at your class and of course it must be the class itself that is broken. Sure, skalds have some weaknesses, but so does every class. If played well, skalds are a very strong class.<br>
<br>
&quot;Skalds' future value in RvR shouldn't be compared solely to their previous value in RvR. It should be compared to all the other classes. An improvement from 'poor' to 'ok' shouldn't really be the goal. In any case, based on responses like this to previous reports it most likely translates to: &quot;We think you're fine despite your protestations--issue closed.&quot;&quot;<br>
<br>
Why shouldn't it? Skalds, previous to 1.65, were a decent class with some flaws that, if changed, would turn them into a good class. They changed spell resists and gave us a reason to keep damage song on. They gave us a few extra hps and I believe the class is where it needs to be. If you give skalds much more, they will be too powerful. I mean, what more do you want? You get speed, instant CC, instant DDs, decent melee damage, resist shouts, damage add, heal song (which is useful in non-combat situations). Now that the shouts are not overly resisted, I find myself doing close to 800 dmg on my first round of combat on soft targets.<br>
<br>
&quot;You've got to be kidding on this one. The QA folks should have 2 years worth of data collected on this already. Everyone that's ever played a skald has complained about this. How many times does this need to be reported on every forum, and for how many years? I think I've probably seen this mentioned on every board it could be mentioned on--I've even seen it on the IGN server boards. This sounds a little like stonewalling. If it can't be fixed, just tell us and we'll drop the subject. Acting like you've never heard of the problem paints a much less attractive picture of Mythic.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yeah the pulse dropping is annoying. No arguments here.<br>
<br>
&quot;Skalds asked for this a long time ago. It was then given to Paladins who didn't ask for it at the time. I remember this vividly. We're still incredulous.&quot;<br>
<br>
Give me a break. At the time those were added, Skalds were among the most powerful classes in the game (pre-SC'd armor, pre-realm abilities). People were still calling for nerfs to skalds at the time. SC and RAs hurt skalds a lot.<br>
<br>
&quot;These 17 points of parry are the only &quot;defense&quot; a skald has, making them (defensively) one of the worst Warrior/Rogue classes in the game. In high level RvR this can't even be considered a defense. If that's how Mythic intends the class to be then case-closed. If not, then somebody needs to look at our defensive abilities. It does lend itself well to the current &quot;cookie cutter&quot; outlook for Skalds. That may also be as intended by Mythic.&quot;<br>
<br>
Don't expect anything more. giving us more spec points means you will see Skalds running around with 50 sword, 50 Bsongs and utterly destroying people. Giving us speccable shield is a joke. We don't have the spec points to make it even close to useful without gimping our other, more important, spec lines. We are a melee hybrid. We are designed to be damage dealers with some utility, not defensive tanks. Everything is a trade-off in this game. Skalds don't get a lot of defense, nor tank RAs like determination, but they get a lot of things to help make up for it.<br>
<br>
I am getting tired of hearing the bitching and moaning about Skalds. They are a great class. Any improvements to them might overpower them. Now I do agree that FoG needs to be made into a RA on the level of BoF or SoS, but that is to balance Midgard and not Skalds. I always hear that Skalds wouldn't be chosen to be in groups if they didnt' have speed. Well, they do have speed. That isn't going to change. Skalds are less powerful in melee primarily because they have speed. It is a tradeoff. Honestly, just be happy that skalds are a viable class that are not just a second-rate tank that isn't picked period over pure melees like Thanes. They are a second rate tank that is necessary for a group to function properly. They get the added bonus of doing a lot of damage. <p>Sligg - 51 - Skald *Bedevere*<br>
<br>
Hungry Hungry Hippos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aurensirramalot>AurenSirRamAlot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Auren/fullsize/shield.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/16/03 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Defense – While the recent changes helped our Offense, and the extra HP helped our survivability a bit, we still suffer from low defense. Parry being our only means of defensive speccing does not return enough value to warrant losing offensive ability. This is probably an issue with most classes that have lower defense and the ability to spec Parry as well. <br>
<br>
<br>
