 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorsonalarik>Thorson Alarik</A> at: 12/18/03 3:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sligg0rz>Sligg0rz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/18/03 9:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Great Job!</span><hr size=1> Wow, the minstrel comment was kind of an aside comment, but the fact that you spent virtually your entire post on it vaidates the rest of my argument. <br>
<br>
I will boil it down to a short and simple comparison:<br>
<br>
You are operating under a different philosphy that I am. My argument that, aside from SoS, the skald is a better class than the minstrel is based on how I RvR:<br>
<br>
Either solo or in a well balanced group. That is pretty much 99% of what I do. <br>
<br>
I have played both classes to high realm ranks and have a pretty good idea of their strengths and weaknesses. I wish I didn't have to spend too much time on this because it isn't really part of my original argument other than a simple  side comment, but I guess I will go into it a bit.<br>
<br>
When I say survivability, I am not specifically speaking about pure defense. Minstrels might have an edge there, but not much of one if at all. Rather I am speaking about their status as a priority target because of SoS. Minstrels generally die quickly against good groups.<br>
<br>
Minstrel crowd control seems to be superior on the surface, but when you consider that in a good group a minstrel will only be mezzing in emergencies and generally late in the battle as most people will be mez immune, things begin to unravel. The instant stun sounds great, but as a minstrel I really didn't use it much except on tanks as a peeling tool because I wanted to wait for healers and casters to get melee slammed because it lasted a lot longer. I think the insta stun is really a way to stop runners and peel. Thats it. Otherwise it is a nuisance at best. The AE mez is inconsequential. I love it when a minstrel AE mezzes me. Doesn't last very long and makes me immune for most of the rest of the battle. A good minstrel in a good group won't bother. The single target mez is decent because you can move while casting it, but you brought up the &quot;stun, then mez&quot; method of CCing, but the problem is that with capped resists the minstrel cannot get off his mez on anyone with an instant spell of any kind. In all the time I played a skald I have never once had a minstrel stun then get off his mez without me interrupting it. As a minstrel that only worked against slow players. I like the skald toolset better because you get 3 different choices. The mez is helpful in some situations ONLY because it is a shout. If a minstrel doesn't get mezzed early on in a fight I mez him so they can't SoS. The instant snare is by far the most useful of the CC options because it has range, interrupts and lasts a long time. Another understated benefit of the skald is his ability to use snare styles. The minstrel has one snare style and it is in a chain off of their no &quot;to hit&quot; detaunt in the thrust line. Most minstrels use blades in the first place. Skalds have access to reasonably accessible snare styles in every weapon line, especially Hammer. I use sword, but I still have access to a side style snare which I get off more than you might guess and the one off the assault chain, which I use a lot. I personally have found that the skald skillset in this case is more applicable to fighting in groups and being good at it.<br>
<br>
Now, even if minstrels have an edge in the survivability line and you can argue that they are roughly equal in terms of CC, skalds make up for it with far superior damage. Minstrel damage even with higher weaponspec is mediocre at best. Skald melee damage is mediocre at worst and extremely good at best. You cannot find a minstrel that can take down a caster in one round of combat. You just can't do it. I do it routinely on my skald. Minstrels are terrible at taking down a solo target in the midst of a battle if they need to. Skalds are very capable of this and in playing a Skald this ability has dramatically changed the way I played the game from someone blindly assisting to someone that can keep 2-3 targets occupied while taking down a healer or caster that is causing trouble. <br>
<br>
I dunno. I just find it funny when skalds complain about minstrels being so much better when I have dueled dozens and never had one take me below 50% life in a 1 vs 1 fight. And beyond that they really don't bring much more to a group than a Skald. I think damage add is more important than ablative chant when you factor BoF into the equation. Otherwise they are both things that really won't change the outcome of battles. Power song is in the same boat as Heal song. Neither are useful in combat. So really what it boils down to is this in terms of group benefits that actually affect the outcome of a battle:<br>
<br>
Skalds: Damage add, resists, instant medium duration CC<br>
<br>
Minstrels: Ablative chant, castable medium duration CC<br>
<br>
I dunno. I think Skalds are pretty close to minstrels on that. The fact if the matter is that Minstrels are SUPPOSED to be a more group oriented class, but they don't have skalds beat by much. The resist chants are great if you have 2 skalds in a group. Aug Healers are extremely rare and it is nice to have a body or energy chant going.<br>
<br>
&quot;skalds CAN obtain decent damage with great gear + buffs<br>
skalds are only moderately needed in rvr anymore (crocodile tears ring makes it so you need 1 skald for whole army now, further decreasing the reasons to group skalds)&quot;<br>
<br>
What kind of garbage group would go anywhere without their own skald? Croc ring is nice, but I can't see any decent group leaving the portal keep depending on someone else for their speed. This might be nice for someone who likes to zerg their way around the frontier, but that isn't me, nor most decent players I know.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Skald shout being reduced to 15 second recast certainly was a nice change, but the fact that minst, in the common spec also got a lvl 50 dd at the same time could hardly be considered beneficial to the balance of the two classes. it remains a cold hard fact that the &quot;support based&quot; minst class can kick the crap out of the melee based combat class (skald) if they are played by anyone with even a reasonable amount of talent.&quot;<br>
<br>
You are out of your mind. Solo minstrels are easy RPs. If you as a skald have lost to a minstrel I have to question if you know what you are doing. They are not a challenge at all. The only skalds I beat solo on my minstrels were stupid ones with poor reflexes, which luckily for me, happened to be 95% of them. I am seriously laughing out loud hearing you say that a minstrel can kick the crap out of a skald.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think your assessment that people are whining about skalds is way off, i think you've gotten a inflated view of their effectiveness, that has thus skewed your analysis.&quot;<br>
<br>
The only thing that has inflated my view of skalds is my ability to play one well. I honestly look at those of you complaining and moaning about Skalds as people who probably don't play the class very well. There are some people who say &quot;The class is good, but there are a couple things that could be looked at.&quot; Fine, I can see that and agree to a point, but based on my experience with the class and about 7 million realm points worth of  other classes, I just don't see skalds as a class deserving of the negativity I see coming from its players. It is a good class. If the best you can do is take one sentence from a post I made and turn this thread into a &quot;WHAAAAAA MINSTRELS HAVE THIS AND WE DON'T&quot;, then I have to say your attitude about this is all wrong. Minstrels are flashier than Skalds, but most of it is fluff in real RvR. The fact that my skald does close to twice the amount of damage my minstrel did (both equipped with the best items in the game), is enough for me to say that all the fluff that minstrels doesn't make skalds a woefully inferior class.<br>
<br>
On a side note, the only thing the Croc Ring will be good for is zerging and if a zerg has speed the only thing it will do is speed them more quickly to places where we can farm them. <p>Sligg - 51 - Skald *Bedevere*<br>
<br>
RR7.X<br>
